observations.recommendation:
We recommended the Management to require:
a. The Inventory Committee to conduct thorough review and physical count of the inventories and PPE by establishing its actual conditions and whereabouts, and come up with the RPCI and RPCPPE;
b. The Inventory Committee to adhere with the submission of RPCI for the first and second semesters not later than July 31 and January 31, respectively, and the annual RPCPPE not later than January 31 of each year to the Audit Team for subsequent review;
c. The Supply and Property Unit and Accounting Office to strengthen its system of maintaining its accounting and property records such as SCs, PCs, SLCs, PPELCs, RPCI and RPCPPE to facilitate periodic reconciliation of these records to ensure reliability of the inventories and PPE account balances as presented in the Financial Statements of the Municipality.
d. The Municipal Accountant and Other Officers concerned should provide for the depreciation on the depreciable assets. The Property Supply Officer should ensure that the Property Custodian keeps and maintains updated Property Card for each PPE account to readily provide pertinent data, thus facilitate the preparation of the Schedule of Depreciation which shall be the basis of recording in the books of accounts the appropriate depreciation expenses pertaining to the current year which should be charged against its appropriate depreciation expense accounts. These are necessary in order to present fairly the PPE accounts which its corresponding Accumulated Depreciation Expense Accounts in FS.
